<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<simulation id="EnzymeCatalysis" version="1" simulatorVersion="09" date="12/15/08">
    <name>&lt;b&gt;Enzyme Catalysis&lt;/b&gt;</name>
    <intro filename=""/>
    <debugger state="on"/> 
    <steps>
        <step id="create">
            <actions>
                <action event="create" name="theexplainer"  url="tools/text_explainer2.swf"  x="0" y="35" xscale="1"  yscale="1"/>
                <action event="create" name="thegrapher" url="tools/graphPointsENZ.swf" x="333" y="270" xscale="1" yscale="1" /> 
                <action event="create" name="beaker" url="swfs/beakerplain.swf"  x="350" y="5" xscale="2"  yscale="1.25"/> 
                <action event="create" name="box1" url="tools/ligandBox09.swf"  x="358" y="31" xscale=".8"  yscale=".8"/>
                <action event="create" name="StoPCast" url="swfs/ActivationcastKey.swf"  x="350" y="335" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
                <action event="create" name="StoPequation" url="swfs/Activationequation.swf"  x="340" y="365" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
                <action event="settimer" timer='12' advance='yes' resettimer='0' /><!--pause briefly to let the objects load, then continue-->
                
            </actions>
            <objects tutor="">
                <object name="theexplainer" state="visible">
                    <title> </title>
                    <text>&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Simulation of Enzyme Catalysis with a Beaker"
                    </text>                  
                </object>
            </objects>
            <nextbutton text="next" state="0"/>
            <prevbutton text="Back" state="0"/>
        </step>
        <step id="Uncatalyzed Reaction">
            <actions>
                <action event="record light"/>
                <action event="create" name="Energydiagram1" url="swfs/ActivationEnergy.swf"  x="520" y="300" xscale=".9" yscale=".9" />
            </actions>
            <objects tutor="">
                <object name="beaker" state="visible"/>
                <object name="theexplainer" state="visible">
                    <title>Uncatalyzed Reaction </title>
                    <text>In order to understand why enzyme catalyzed reactions are important we need to understand the difference in the energy diagrams that exists between a uncatalyzed and catalyzed reaction.
                        
In the simulation to the right you see the uncatalyzed reaction in which S is the substrate and P is the product.
                        
Press "Continue" to see the simulation run.
                    </text>                  
                </object>
                <object name="StoPequation" state="hilight" action="1" />
                <object name="StoPCast" state="visible" />
            </objects>
            <nextbutton text="Continue" state="1"/>
            <prevbutton text="Back" state="0"/>
        </step>
        <step id="Uncatalyzed Simulation">
            <actions>
                <action event="initialize" name="box1" params="leftBorder=10,rightBorder=390,topBorder=10,bottomBorder=250,leftBorder2=10,rightBorder2=390,topBorder2=10,bottomBorder2=250">
                    <molecules>                         
                        <molecule numMolecules= "0" myID="0"/>     <!--This is a fudge if only one molecule seems to need to be here-->
                        <molecule numMolecules= "0"  numbound= "0" velocity= "40"  cast= "ligandblue"   angle1= "45" angle2= "315" rotationVelocity="5"  rotation="30" x="100" y="100" Xoffset="5" Yoffset="5"  mytype="molecule"  myID="1"  polarity = "0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0" mybounce="true" seperateinto="productidl?3,productidm?2,productidp?4,Kd?50,k?1000,Kcat?.02"/>           
                        <molecule numMolecules= "1"  numbound= "0" velocity= "40"  cast= "enzymeinv" angle1= "45" angle2= "315" rotationVelocity="5"  rotation="30" x="200" y="200" Xoffset="5" Yoffset="5"  mytype="molecule"  myID="2"  polarity = "0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0" mybounce="true" />                                   
                        <molecule numMolecules= "50"  numbound= "0" velocity= "60"  cast= "ligandblue"   angle1= "45" angle2= "315" rotationVelocity="5"  rotation="30"   x="50" y="50" Xoffset="5" Yoffset="5" mytype="ligand"  myID="3"   polarity = "0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0" mybounce="true" bindswith="molecule2.pocket1.bound,Kd?25,k?500,productidm?1"/>
                        <molecule numMolecules=  "0"  numbound= "0" velocity= "60"  cast= "product"  angle1= "45" angle2= "315" rotationVelocity="5"  rotation="30"   x="100" y="100" Xoffset="5" Yoffset="5" mytype="ligand"  myID="4"    polarity = "0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0" mybounce="true" isproduct="1" />     <!--isproduct="1"-->
                    </molecules>
                </action>
                <action event="initialize" name="opener" />
                <!-- this line is fudge to unpause the world which should not be paused -->
                <action event="record light"/>
                <action event="create" name="equation1" url="tools/equation1.swf"  x="350" y="295" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
                <action event="create" name="equation2" url="tools/equation2.swf"  x="500" y="290" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
                <action event="create" name="userdata" url="tools/userdataKD.swf"  x="340" y="250" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
                <action event="create" name="inputs1" url="tools/DisplayVariable09.swf"  x="525" y="300" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
                <action event="create" name="inputs2" url="tools/DisplayVariable09.swf"  x="575" y="300" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
                <action event="create" name="inputs3" url="tools/DisplayVariable09.swf"  x="365" y="300" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
                <action event="create" name="inputs4" url="tools/DisplayVariable09.swf"  x="415" y="300" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
                <action event="create" name="inputs5" url="tools/DisplayVariable09.swf"  x="465" y="300" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
                <action event="create" name="castKey1" url="tools/castKey1.swf"  x="360" y="265" xscale=".65" yscale=".65" />
                <action event="create" name="castKey2" url="tools/castKey2.swf"  x="530" y="265" xscale=".65" yscale=".65" />
            </actions>
            <objects tutor="">
                <object name="beaker" state="visible"/>
                <object name="theexplainer" state="visible">
                    <title>Uncatalyzed Simulation</title>
                    <text>As you can see in the simulation very little product is created. This is primarily due to the large activation energy. 
                        
From the energy diagram you should realize that the probability of a S spontaneously having enough energy to move toward products is very very small evan though P is energetically favored .
                        
Click "Next" to see how this changes with an enzyme present.
                    </text>                  
                </object>
                <object name="Energydiagram1" state="visible" />
                <object name="box1" state="visible" />
                <object name="StoPCast" state="visible" />
                <object name="StoPequation" state="hilight" action="1" />
            </objects>
            <nextbutton text="Next" state="1"/>
            <prevbutton text="Back" state="0"/>
        </step>
        <step id="Catalyzed Equation">
            <actions>
                <action event="record light"/>
                <action event="unload" name="Energydiagram1"/> 
                <action event="unload" name="StoPCast"/> 
                <action event="unload" name="StoPequation"/> 
                <action event="create" name="Energydiagram2" url="swfs/ESActivationEnergy.swf"  x="450" y="325" xscale=".85" yscale=".85" />
            </actions>
            <objects tutor="">
                <object name="beaker" state="visible"/>
                <object name="theexplainer" state="visible">
                    <title>Catalyzed Equation </title>
                    <text>In this example, the &lt;b&gt;E&lt;/b&gt; stands for the Enzyme and &lt;b&gt;S&lt;/b&gt; is the substrate.  This enzyme will act a a catalyst to aid in the production of the product &lt;b&gt;P&lt;/b&gt;.
&lt;br&gt;As you can see in the equation, the Enzyme and Substrate are in a reversible equilibrium with the &lt;b&gt;[ES]&lt;/b&gt;, or "Michaelis complex".
                        
Press "Continue" to see this simulation run with it potential energy diagram.
                    </text>                  
                </object>
                <object name="userinput" state="hilight"/>
                <object name="slider1" state="invisible"/>
                <object name="equation1" state="hilight" action="1" />
                <object name="equation2" state="visible" action="1" />
                <object name="castKey1" state="visible" />
                <object name="castKey2" state="visible" />
                <object name="inputs2" capture="yes" state="invisible"/>
                <object name="inputs1" capture="yes" state="invisible" />
            </objects>
            <nextbutton text="Continue" state="1"/>
            <prevbutton text="Back" state="0"/>
        </step>
        <step id="Catalyzed Simulation">
            <actions>
                <action event="record light"/>
                <action event="initialize" name="box1" params="leftBorder=0,rightBorder=475,topBorder=0,bottomBorder=250,leftBorder2=0,rightBorder2=475,topBorder2=0,bottomBorder2=250">
                    <molecules>  
                        <molecule numMolecules= "0" myID="0"/>     <!--This is a fudge if only one molecule seems to need to be here--> 
                        <molecule numMolecules= "0"  numbound= "0" velocity= "40"  cast= "enzymeBound"   angle1= "45" angle2= "315" rotationVelocity="5"  rotation="30" x="100" y="100" Xoffset="5" Yoffset="5"  mytype="molecule"  myID="1"  polarity = "0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0" mybounce="true" seperateinto="productidl?3,productidm?2,productidp?4,Kd?25,k?1000,Kcat?.1"/>            
                        <molecule numMolecules= "2"  numbound= "0" velocity= "40"  cast= "enzyme" angle1= "45" angle2= "315" rotationVelocity="5"  rotation="30" x="200" y="200" Xoffset="50" Yoffset="50"  mytype="molecule"  myID="2"  polarity = "0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0" mybounce="true" />            
                        <molecule numMolecules= "0"  numbound= "0" velocity= "60"  cast= "ligandblue"   angle1= "45" angle2= "315" rotationVelocity="5"  rotation="30"   x="100" y="100" Xoffset="50" Yoffset="50" mytype="ligand"  myID="3"   polarity = "0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0" mybounce="true" bindswith="molecule2.pocket1.free,Kd?25,k?1000,productidm?1" />   
                        <molecule numMolecules=  "0"  numbound= "0" velocity= "60"  cast= "product"  angle1= "45" angle2= "315" rotationVelocity="5"  rotation="30"   x="100" y="100" Xoffset="5" Yoffset="5" mytype="ligand"  myID="4"    polarity = "0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0" mybounce="true"  />     <!--isproduct="1"-->
                        <!--   don't add new bindswith parameters until we completely implement the parser for this-->
                    </molecules>
                </action>
                <action event="initialize" name="inputs1" params="simulator=box1,thevariable=M4,thevalue=0" data="0"/>             
                <action event="initialize" name="inputs2" params="simulator=box1,thevariable=M2,thevalue=0" data="0"/> 
                <action event="initialize" name="inputs3" params="simulator=box1,thevariable=M2,thevalue=0" data="0"/> 
                <action event="initialize" name="inputs4" params="simulator=box1,thevariable=M3,thevalue=0" data="0"/> 
                <action event="initialize" name="inputs5" params="simulator=box1,thevariable=M1,thevalue=0" data="0"/> 
                <action event="initialize" name="Toff" data="T off" params="_root.box1.bindstrength"  />
                <action event="initialize" name="Kd" data="Kd" params="_root.box1.Kd"  />
                <action event="initialize" name="slider1" params="L total" data="40"/>
                <action event="record all"/>
            </actions>
            <objects tutor="">
                <object name="box1" state="visible"/>
                <object name="beaker" state="visible"/>
                <object name="theexplainer" state="visible">
                    <title>Catalyzed Simulation </title>
                    <text>With the enzyme present the activation energy for the forward reaction is lowered. This allows for more substrates to be converted into products.
                        
Now that we understand that the enzyme lowers the activation energy for the reaction, lets look at the rates of reaction for both the catalyzed and uncatalyzed reactions.
                        
Click "Next" to compare the two rate curves.
                    </text>                  
                </object>
                <object name="userinput" state="hilight"/>
                <object name="slider1" state="invisible"/>
                <object name="equation1" state="hilight" action="1" />
                <object name="equation2" state="visible" action="1" />
                <object name="castKey1" state="visible" />
                <object name="castKey2" state="visible" />
                <object name="Energydiagram2" state="visible" />
                <object name="inputs2" capture="yes" state="invisible"/>
                <object name="inputs1" capture="yes" state="invisible" />
            </objects>
            <nextbutton text="Next" state="1"/>
            <prevbutton text="Back" state="0"/>
        </step>
        <step id="Rates of Reaction">
            <actions>
                <action event="record light"/>
                <action event="scale" name="Energydiagram2" x="450" y="200" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
            </actions>
            <objects tutor="">
                <object name="theexplainer" state="visible">
                    <title>Rates of Reaction </title>
                    <text>Based on what we already have learned, adding a enzyme causes a slight change in the activation energy of the forward reaction.
                        
Looking at the two rate curves you can see a very large jump in rate for the enzyme catalyzed reaction. This large jump is attributed to the lowering of the activation energy. 
                        
Notice that this relationship is not linear but rather exponential.????????
                        
Having seen and understanding the difference between catalyzed and uncatlayzed reactions lets look at some of the factors that affect the more favorable enzyme catalyzed reaction.
                    </text>                  
                </object>
                <object name="Energydiagram2" state="visible"/>
            </objects>
            <nextbutton text="Next" state="1"/>
            <prevbutton text="Back" state="0"/>
        </step>
        <step id="Changing Substrate Concentration">
            <actions>
                <action event="unload" name="Energydiagram2"/>
                <action event="record light"/>
            </actions>
            <objects tutor="">
                <object name="Energydiagram2" state="visible" />
                <object name="theexplainer" state="visible">
                    <title>Changing Substrate Concentration</title>
                    <text>Using the simulation explore how changing the concentration of substrate will affect the velocity of the reaction. 
   
By clicking on the different substrate concentrations you will create a graph of velocity vs concentration. Make sure to watch the simulation for each concentration, it should show some insight as to what is happening to change the velocity.
                        
Once you have finished exploring click "Continue".
                    </text>                  
                </object>
            </objects>
            <nextbutton text="Continue" state="1"/>
            <prevbutton text="Back" state="0"/>
        </step>
        <step id="Changing Concentration Summation">
            <actions>
                <action event="record light"/>
                <action event="initialize" name="thegrapher"  data="1" params="moleculeID=,ligandID=3,productID="/>
                <action event="reset" name="box1" params="2"/>
                <action event="reset" name="box1" params="1"/>
                <action event="reset" name="box1" params="3"/> 
                <action event="reset" name="box1" params="4"/> 
                <action event="sendmessage" name="box1" params="msg=changeParam,param1=M*,param2=12,param3=2,x=100,y=160,Xoffset=0,Yoffset=0" /> 
                <action event="sendmessage" name="box1" params="msg=changeParam,param1=M*,param2=0,param3=3,x=100,y=160,Xoffset=0,Yoffset=0" /> 

                <action event="record light"/>
            </actions>
            <objects tutor="">
                <object name="thegrapher" state="visible" />
                <object name="box1" state="visible"/>
                <object name="beaker" state="visible"/>
                <object name="userinput" state="hilight"/>
                <object name="slider1" state="invisible"/>
                <object name="equation1" state="hilight" action="1" />
                <object name="equation2" state="visible" action="1" />
                <object name="castKey1" state="visible" />
                <object name="castKey2" state="visible" />
                <object name="inputs2" capture="yes" state="invisible"/>
                <object name="inputs1" capture="yes" state="invisible" />
                <object name="theexplainer" state="visible">
                    <title>Changing Concentration Summation</title>
                    <text>As the amount of substrate increases the enzyme spends much less time looking for substrate and most of its time converting them into product.
                        
However, at a certain point the enzymes become saturated with substrate. At this point we have reached Vmax. Since the enzymes are in constant contact with substrate they are converting them as quickly as possible and we cannot increase the rate or reaction by adding substrate. 
                    </text>                  
                </object>
            </objects>
            <nextbutton text="Continue" state="1"/>
            <prevbutton text="Back" state="0"/>
        </step>
        <step id="prepare to exit">
            
            <objects tutor="">
                
            </objects>
            <actions>
                <action event="unload" name="box1"/>
                <action event="settimer" timer='6' advance='yes' resettimer='0' />
            </actions>
            <nextbutton text="Next" state="0"/>
            <prevbutton text="Back" state="0"/>
        </step>
        
        <step id="exit">
            
            <objects tutor="">
                
            </objects>
            <actions>
                <action event="record light"/>
                <action event="exit" />
            </actions>
        </step>
    </steps>
</simulation>